    {# ══════ GS1 ══════ #}
    <div class="mn-paper" id="gs1" style="--mn-color:#9f1239;">
      <div class="mn-paper__header" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#881337 0%,#9f1239 100%)">
        <div class="mn-paper__info"><h2 class="mn-paper__title">GS Paper 1 — History, Geography, Society</h2><p class="mn-paper__sub">Indian Heritage & Culture | Modern History | World History | Geography | Indian Society</p></div>
        <span class="mn-paper__marks">250</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs1-1"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🏛️</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">History & Culture</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">7 units | 47 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs1-1"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Salient aspects of Art Forms, Literature and Architecture from ancient to modern times. Modern Indian history from mid-18th century — significant events, personalities, issues. The Freedom Struggle. Post-independence consolidation. World History from 18th century — industrial revolution, world wars, colonization, decolonization, political philosophies.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links">
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/ancient-india/" class="mn-link">Ancient India <span class="mn-link-count">8 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/medieval-india/" class="mn-link">Medieval India <span class="mn-link-count">8 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/modern-india/" class="mn-link">Modern India <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/freedom-struggle/" class="mn-link">Freedom Struggle <span class="mn-link-count">8 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/post-independence-india/" class="mn-link">Post-Independence <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/indian-culture/" class="mn-link">Indian Culture <span class="mn-link-count">5 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/history-culture/world-history/" class="mn-link">World History <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs1-2"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🌍</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Geography</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">4 units | 12 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs1-2"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Salient features of world's physical geography. Distribution of key natural resources across the world. Factors responsible for location of primary, secondary, and tertiary sector industries. Important geophysical phenomena. Changes in critical geographical features and effects on flora and fauna.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links">
            <a href="/subjects/geography/physical-geography/" class="mn-link">Physical Geo <span class="mn-link-count">2 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/geography/indian-geography/" class="mn-link">Indian Geo <span class="mn-link-count">5 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/geography/human-economic-geography/" class="mn-link">Human & Economic <span class="mn-link-count">3 ch</span></a>
            <a href="/subjects/geography/world-geography/" class="mn-link">World Geo <span class="mn-link-count">2 ch</span></a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs1-3"><span class="mn-subj__icon">👥</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Indian Society</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 8 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs1-3"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Salient features of Indian Society, Diversity of India. Role of women and women's organizations. Population and associated issues. Poverty and developmental issues. Urbanization. Effects of globalization. Social empowerment, communalism, regionalism & secularism.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/society/indian-society/" class="mn-link">Indian Society <span class="mn-link-count">8 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ══════ GS2 ══════ #}
    <div class="mn-paper" id="gs2" style="--mn-color:#7c3aed;">
      <div class="mn-paper__header" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#5b21b6 0%,#7c3aed 100%)">
        <div class="mn-paper__info"><h2 class="mn-paper__title">GS Paper 2 — Polity, Governance, IR</h2><p class="mn-paper__sub">Constitution | Governance | Social Justice | International Relations</p></div>
        <span class="mn-paper__marks">250</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs2-1"><span class="mn-subj__icon">⚖️</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Polity, Governance & Social Justice</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 14 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs2-1"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Indian Constitution — historical underpinnings, evolution, features, amendments, basic structure. Functions of Union and States. Federal structure issues. Parliament and State Legislatures. Executive and Judiciary. Governance, transparency, accountability, e-governance. Welfare schemes. Development processes — role of NGOs, SHGs.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/polity/constitutional-polity/" class="mn-link">Constitutional Polity <span class="mn-link-count">14 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs2-2"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🤝</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">International Relations</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 6 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs2-2"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">India and its neighbourhood relations. Bilateral, regional and global groupings involving India. Effect of policies of developed and developing countries on India's interests. Indian diaspora. Important international institutions, agencies and fora — structure, mandate.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/international-relations/global-relations/" class="mn-link">Global Relations <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ══════ GS3 ══════ #}
    <div class="mn-paper" id="gs3" style="--mn-color:#0369a1;">
      <div class="mn-paper__header" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#075985 0%,#0369a1 100%)">
        <div class="mn-paper__info"><h2 class="mn-paper__title">GS Paper 3 — Economy, S&T, Env, Security</h2><p class="mn-paper__sub">Economic Development | Agriculture | S&T | Environment | DM | Internal Security</p></div>
        <span class="mn-paper__marks">250</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs3-1"><span class="mn-subj__icon">💰</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Indian Economy</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 10 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs3-1"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Indian Economy — planning, mobilization of resources, growth, development, employment. Inclusive growth. Government Budgeting. Land reforms. Changes in industrial policy. Infrastructure: Energy, Ports, Roads, Airports, Railways. Investment models. Major crops, cropping patterns, irrigation. MSP, PDS, food security. Food processing industries. Economics of animal-rearing.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/economy/indian-economy/" class="mn-link">Indian Economy <span class="mn-link-count">10 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs3-2"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🔬</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Science & Technology</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 7 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs3-2"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Developments in S&T — applications and effects in everyday life. Achievements of Indians in S&T. Indigenization of technology. Awareness in IT, Space, Computers, robotics, nano-tech, bio-tech. Issues relating to intellectual property rights.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/science-tech/science-technology/" class="mn-link">Science & Technology <span class="mn-link-count">7 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs3-3"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🌿</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Environment & Ecology</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 6 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs3-3"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Conservation, environmental pollution and degradation. Environmental impact assessment.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/environment/ecology-environment/" class="mn-link">Ecology & Environment <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs3-4"><span class="mn-subj__icon">⚠️</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Disaster Management</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 6 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs3-4"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Disaster and disaster management.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/disaster-management/dm-framework/" class="mn-link">DM Framework <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs3-5"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🛡️</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Internal Security</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 6 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs3-5"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Linkages between development and spread of extremism. Role of external state and non-state actors. Challenges through communication networks. Role of media and social networking. Cyber security. Money laundering. Security challenges in border areas. Organized crime-terrorism linkages. Various security forces and agencies.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/security/internal-security/" class="mn-link">Internal Security <span class="mn-link-count">6 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ══════ GS4 ══════ #}
    <div class="mn-paper" id="gs4" style="--mn-color:#854d0e;">
      <div class="mn-paper__header" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#713f12 0%,#854d0e 100%)">
        <div class="mn-paper__info"><h2 class="mn-paper__title">GS Paper 4 — Ethics, Integrity & Aptitude</h2><p class="mn-paper__sub">Theory (125 marks) + Case Studies (125 marks)</p></div>
        <span class="mn-paper__marks">250</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mn-subj"><div class="mn-subj__head" data-t="gs4-1"><span class="mn-subj__icon">🧭</span><div class="mn-subj__info"><p class="mn-subj__title">Ethics, Attitude, Aptitude & Case Studies</p><span class="mn-subj__meta">1 unit | 8 chapters</span></div><span class="mn-subj__arrow"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></div>
        <div class="mn-subj__body" id="gs4-1"><p class="mn-subj__syllabus">Ethics and Human Interface — essence, determinants, consequences. Human Values — lessons from great leaders. Attitude — content, structure, function. Aptitude and foundational values for civil service. Emotional intelligence. Contributions of moral thinkers from India and world. Probity in governance. Codes of ethics, citizen's charters. Corruption challenges. Case studies on above issues.</p>
          <div class="mn-subj__links"><a href="/subjects/ethics/ethics-aptitude/" class="mn-link">Ethics & Aptitude <span class="mn-link-count">8 ch</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ══════ ESSAY ══════ #}
    <div class="mn-paper" id="essay" style="--mn-color:#b45309;">
      <div class="mn-paper__header" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#92400e 0%,#b45309 100%)">
        <div class="mn-paper__info"><h2 class="mn-paper__title">Essay Paper</h2><p class="mn-paper__sub">2 essays (1 from each section) | ~1000-1200 words each | 3 hours</p></div>
        <span class="mn-paper__marks">250</span>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:var(--space-4);background:var(--color-surface);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md);font-size:var(--text-sm);line-height:1.7;color:var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-2);"><strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Section A:</strong> Philosophical, abstract, social themes</p>
        <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-2);"><strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Section B:</strong> Socio-economic, political, governance themes</p>
        <p style="margin:0;"><strong style="color:var(--color-text);">Structure:</strong> Intro → Multi-dimensional body (social, economic, political, philosophical) → Conclusion with personal touch. Use quotes, data, examples. Credit given for effective and exact expression.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:var(--space-4) var(--space-4) 0;">
        <a href="/essay/" class="btn btn--accent btn--sm">View Essay Paper Hub →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ══════ STRATEGY ══════ #}
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="strategy">Answer Writing Strategy</h2>

    <div class="mn-answer">
      <div class="mn-answer-card"><h4>10-Mark Answer (150 words, ~7 min)</h4><p><strong>Intro</strong> (1-2 lines) — Define concept or context<br><strong>Body</strong> (8-10 lines) — 3-4 points with examples/data<br><strong>Conclusion</strong> (1-2 lines) — Way forward or balanced view</p></div>
      <div class="mn-answer-card"><h4>15-Mark Answer (250 words, ~13 min)</h4><p><strong>Intro</strong> (2-3 lines) — Context + define the issue<br><strong>Body</strong> (15-18 lines) — Multi-dimensional: economic, social, political<br><strong>Diagram</strong> — Add one if relevant (saves words, scores marks)<br><strong>Conclusion</strong> (2-3 lines) — Balanced view + way forward</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mn-tips">
      <div class="mn-tip"><span class="mn-tip__icon">📰</span><div><p class="mn-tip__title">Current Affairs in every answer</p><p class="mn-tip__desc">Recent schemes, judgments, data, committees. This separates average from top-scoring answers. <a href="https://ujiyari.com/editorial/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read Ujiyari editorials daily.</a></p></div></div>
      <div class="mn-tip"><span class="mn-tip__icon">📐</span><div><p class="mn-tip__title">Directive words matter</p><p class="mn-tip__desc">"Discuss" = all sides. "Critically examine" = your conclusion. "Enumerate" = list + explain. Misreading loses marks on content you know.</p></div></div>
      <div class="mn-tip"><span class="mn-tip__icon">✏️</span><div><p class="mn-tip__title">Never skip a question</p><p class="mn-tip__desc">Even 3-4 basic points score 3-5 marks. A blank scores zero. Over 20 questions, that's 60-100 marks difference.</p></div></div>
      <div class="mn-tip"><span class="mn-tip__icon">⏱️</span><div><p class="mn-tip__title">Time discipline</p><p class="mn-tip__desc">20 Qs in 3 hrs = 9 min avg. Budget 7 min for 10-markers, 13 min for 15-markers. Practice with a stopwatch.</p></div></div>
      <div class="mn-tip"><span class="mn-tip__icon">📊</span><div><p class="mn-tip__title">Visual presentation</p><p class="mn-tip__desc">Headings, sub-points, diagrams, flowcharts. Underline keywords. Examiners scan 500+ sheets — make yours stand out.</p></div></div>
      <div class="mn-tip"><span class="mn-tip__icon">✍️</span><div><p class="mn-tip__title">Daily answer writing</p><p class="mn-tip__desc">Write 2-3 answers daily using <a href="https://ujiyari.com/mains-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">I-B-C framework</a>. Speed comes from practice, not shortcuts.</p></div></div>
    </div>

